Must be installed PostgreSQL in system, if not then to make command:

sudo apt-get install postgresql
sudo passwd postgres
sudo -u postgres createuser -P django_login
su postgres
psql template1
CREATE DATABASE picker OWNER admin ENCODING 'UTF8';

Edit the Postgres permissions in /etc/postgres/8.4/pg_hba.conf by adding a line as follows after the postgres user line:
local      django_db   django_login   md5

Then:
sudo /etc/init.d/postgresql-8.4 restart

After installing psycopg:

sudo apt-get install python-psycopg2
pip install psycopg2 or easy_installed psycopg2
sudo apt-get install python-dev postgresql libpq-dev

Edit your settings.py file in the django app directory:
'ENGINE': 'postgresql_psycopg2',
'NAME': 'django_db',
'USER': 'django_login',
'PASSWORD': 'your_password',

python manage.py syncdb



ALTER TABLE capturing_textsite ADD COLUMN text_tsv tsvector;
CREATE TRIGGER tsvectorupdate BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE ON capturing_textsite FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE PROCEDURE tsvector_update_trigger(text_tsv, 'pg_catalog.english', text);
CREATE INDEX capturing_textsite_tsv ON capturing_textsite USING gin(text_tsv);
UPDATE capturing_textsite SET text_tsv=to_tsvector(text);